cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about using neural architecture search (NAS) to automatically design effective neural network architectures for low-level image restoration tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the optimization of neural network architectures, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method on different datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
